claim.claim-text:
1. a combined structure of a sports shoe and a in-line skate comprising at least a shoe body and a in-line wheel device further comprising: 
a base, wherein a wheel placing space is set at a bottom surface and a placing room is set at a rear side, a transverse channel and a lengthwise slot being set at a top surface of said placing room, a guide opening being set at an rear end, a trench being set at a rear lateral side of said base and passing through said placing room, two pair of position columns are respectively set at both sides of a front and rear of said base; 
a control mechanism composed of a control part and a guide part, wherein said control part comprises a push bar, a compression spring and a hollow washer slipped on said push bar, said control part being placed in said guide opening on the rear end of said base; and wherein said guide part comprises a guide arm clipping with a guide bar at a front end and having a trough at a rear end, a first torsion spring setting in said trough, a position bar passing through said trough and a first torsion spring being placed into said transverse channel of said placing room of said base and said guide bar jutting out said trench at both rear sides of said base, a first end of said first torsion spring holding to said trough of said guide bar while a second end of said torsion spring holding to said lengthwise slot, a upper cover being covered above said placing room and said trench such that said control mechanism can be combined at the rear of said base; 
a linkage set comprising more than one link, a plurality of joining holes being set at both ends of said links to be joined for driving motion; 
a position plate with a pair of position holes at both ends, wherein at least one arc slot is set, a plate-hole being set above a concave side of each said at least one arc, a guide slot extending from an end of one of said at least one arc slot; 
a wheel position mechanism comprising at least one turning plate, wherein a twin first holes are set at a top end and a second hole at a bottom end for joining with a wheel, a first breach and a second breach being respectively set at first and second proper position on an upper and lower end of one of said at least one turning plate for clipping; 
wherein said linkage set, said positioning plate and said wheel position mechanism are combined in order at both ends of said base and arranged in homologous state, at least one position pin and a shaft bar passing through said homologous first and second holes at said top end of every said at least one turning plate in said wheel position mechanism, and said at least one arc slot, and said plate-hole above said concave side of said at least one arc slot, and said joined holes at both ends of each said at least one link of said linkage set such that said linkage set, said positioning plate and said wheel position mechanism are combined steadily at both ends of said base, said pair of position holes of said position plate being joined to said pair of position columns at each side of said base such that said position plate be secured steadily to both sides of said base; a second torsion spring being slipped on one of said at least one position pin, a first end of said torsion spring holding to said shaft bar corresponding to said position pin while a second end holding to said placing room of said base; said guide bar jutting out said trench at the rear lateral side of said base passing though said guide slot of said arc slot of said position plate and clipping with said first or said second breach; each of said wheels being joined between each said turning plate of said in-line wheel device and arranged in in-line state; a plurality of components described above composing said combined structure of a sports shoe and a in-line skate.
